name: AMOR (THE STORY OF LOVE)
description: Amorphophallus titanum the Latin name of the corpse flower that we raise in this work. a composing of the word "amor" which means love in Portuguese. Here we highlight an interesting feature of the smelly but rare corpse flower and is liked by many people because of its uniqueness. associated with the word love, it turns out that there are flowers that are not always fragrant but are loved, and are useful for small animals around them. There is an attraction from the other side that brings love.
